  "reference": "Numerics @ a2c4dbf. Args convention (this port's own -- see fixtures/README.md): PlottingPositions.weibull_at takes args = [N, i] (0-based i, analytic PP[i] = (i+1)/(N+1)); PlottingPositions.function_at takes args = [N, alpha, i] (analytic PP[i] = (i+1-alpha)/(N+1-2*alpha)). Both entries are directly oracle-verified via tools/verify_oracles.py even though the formula is closed-form, per this repo's policy of confirming every fixture value against the real C# library.",
